publications.name: Detecting Semantic Clones in Microservices Using Components
publications.description: This paper explores the challenges posed by the growing use of enterprise technologies for decentralized systems, particularly in the context of code clone detection. It emphasizes the need to address duplicated behavior with different syntactic structures, referred to as semantic clones, in large and evolving software codebases. The proposed method utilizes semantic information and targeted enterprise metadata to reason about semantic clones, achieving high accuracy in detection when applied to an established system benchmark and demonstrating applicability to decentralized system evolution through assessment of different system versions.

publications.name: Distributed Text Representations Using Transformers for Noisy Written Language
publications.description: This paper presents a methodology for deriving latent representations for highly noisy text using a character-based approach. Instead of relying on words, the proposed method pre-trains a Transformer model (BERT) on general-purpose language tasks and transfers weights between tasks to obtain representations for input texts. By considering characters as tokens instead of word or sub-word tokenization, the approach aims to produce useful representations for downstream tasks, including the detection of criminal activity in marketplace platforms.

publications.name: Dual Architecture for Name Entity Extraction and Relation Extraction with Applications in Medical Corpora
publications.description: In this paper, the growing interest in automatic knowledge discovery in plain text documents is discussed, emphasizing the relevance of such efforts in the health domain where annotated corpora are scarce. The work utilizes an existing health-oriented Spanish dataset as a starting point, creates an English variant using the same tagging system, and designs two separate architectures for Entity Recognition and Relation Extraction, which outperform previous works in the Spanish dataset and show promising results in the English version.
